We go to Casa Di Pizza whenever we are looking for GREAT Pizza and Wings, south of the border, we have been going for over 10 years. You always get a smile and warm welcome upon arrival. The restaurant atmosphere is always upbeat, clean with various sports on numerous tv's. The bar has many craft beers available and they are happy to offer a small sample prior to your selection, which is a real treat. The wait staff is fabulous. We look forward to seeing Judy, who is always on the ball and does a great job catering to all the tables. The menu is filled with options. What got us hooked on coming, was their kids Pizza option, where for $4.99, the child is brought out their rolled pizza dough, a cup of sauce & cheese, as well as their selected toppings. The kids can make their own pizza, and it gets taken away, cooked and returned. The kids love it, it also comes with a drink and a little dessert. We have been returning for years, partially due to the kids option, partially due to the great prices, and mainly for the amazing quality, great tasting pizza and wings. You can't go wrong with JJs Casa Di Pizza, they have a good thing going, and the pizza taste is truly amazing.

I WAS NOT EXPECTING THIS.... Did you take French in school or did you take Spanish?  Why do I ask? Because you will not understand the meaning of Casa Di PIzza.  See, casa means house.  So you are literally going to a house of pizza here.  Except one thing.  The house itself is not made out of pizza.  I think this is something that can be solved though.  All they have to do is cook a pizza big enough to cover the walls inside and out.  This way it will be like a veneer of pizza engulfing the whole surface of the place.  Then it will truly be a house of pizza.  Until then.  You just gotta look at things differently.  I will help you out.  If you see a business called house of shoes... it doesn't mean the house is made out of shoes.  It just means they sell shoes.  I know it can be confusing.

They have replaced imo good interesting dishes like pizza fries that I craved with fries covered in cheesewiz and bacon called loaded fries that were substantially worse. They are replacing good pizza with various weird pizzas that include way too many raw onions. They are also undercooking said pizza to the point where the dough is only cooked lightly on the bottom.  It's been a drop in quality and I don't think I'll be back at least for a long while with how many places we have downtown. That said it's still edible and the service is good and prices not unreasonable.
